In 1985 Blackstone opened its doors with a staff of four, including the two founders, Peter G. Peterson and Stephen A. Schwarzman, and a balance sheet of $400,000. From these early beginnings, besides big dreams, the founders have held these core beliefs:
  Â   1   In an environment of ever larger firms, the most gifted would desire a more personal setting and would join Blackstone to create exciting new businesses in their fields of expertise.
         Â   2   In a world of giant organizations    with a broad array of services, there was room for a specialized firm with the highest levels of professionalism and integrity, and senior-level attention to clients and relationships.     Â   3   In contrast to the prevailing philosophy  of â€œother peopleâ€™s money,â€ the firm would always put significant amounts of its own money in the investments it made.
         Â   4   We will consistently strive to achieve  superior performance through innovation, uniqueness and excellence.     Â   5  Above all else our people â€” their creativity,   imagination, dedication, teamwork and integrity â€” will be our key assets.
        





