David L. CalhounÂ is a Senior Managing Director and Head of Private Equity Portfolio Operations of Blackstone and a Member of Blackstoneâ€™s Management Committee.
Mr. Calhoun joined Blackstone in January of 2014 and oversees a team within the portfolio operations group focused on creating and driving added value initiatives with Blackstone portfolio company CEOs.Â 
Since the beginning of 2014, Mr. Calhoun serves as Executive Chairman of the Board for Nielsen, a company he joined in 2006 as Chief Executive Officer, shortly after it was acquired by a consortium of private equity investors including Blackstone. Throughout his seven yearsâ€™ tenure, Mr. Calhoun led Nielsenâ€™s transformation into a leading global information and measurement company listed on the New York Stock Exchange (NLSN) and Standard & Poorâ€™s 500 Index.
Before Nielsen, Mr. Calhoun served as Vice Chairman of The General Electric Company and President and Chief Executive Officer of GE Infrastructure, the companyâ€™s largest business unit. During his distinguished twenty-six year tenure at GE, Mr. Calhoun ran multiple business units, including GE Lighting, GE Employers Reinsurance Co., GE Aircraft Engines, and GE Transportation (Aircraft and Rail).Â  Earlier in his career at GE, he held a wide range of operating, finance, and marketing roles across the company, including within GE Plastics and GE Capital.
